  RSP-20260408-S1 slot=1 topic=Hermes Agent
PENDING|RSP-20260408-S1|1|If you're running AI agents in production, you're probably juggling multiple API keys for the same provider. Rate limits, cost spikes, a key going down. It's a mess to manage by hand.  Hermes Agent v0.7.0 just shipped same-provider credential pools. You configure multiple keys, and it rotates them automatically using a least-used strategy. If one key gets a 401, it switches to the next one without missing a beat.  For operators running agents at scale, this is the difference between a setup that survives a traffic spike and one that just falls over.  https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/releases/tag/v2026.4.3
  RSP-20260408-S2 slot=2 topic=OpenClaw GitHub releases
PENDING|RSP-20260408-S2|2|You want to run an AI model, but you don't want to set up a full agent workflow to do it. That's a real friction point for quick tasks, prototyping, or one-off jobs.  OpenClaw 2026.4.8 adds `openclaw infer`, a first-class CLI hub for provider-backed inference. It covers image generation, music, video, web scraping, and embeddings through a single interface, with automatic fallback across providers if one is down or rate-limited.  If you've been avoiding agent frameworks because they felt like overkill, this is the layer underneath that actually matters.  https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/releases/tag/v2026.4.8
  RSP-20260408-S3 slot=3 topic=AI agent ops
PENDING|RSP-20260408-S3|3|Long-running AI workflows have a durability problem. If your agent crashes after 40 minutes of work, you lose everything and start over from scratch. For anything serious, that's not acceptable.  crewAI 1.14.0 adds automatic checkpointing with SQLite storage. The framework saves runtime state as it runs, so if something breaks you can resume from where you left off instead of from the beginning.  The feature also includes guardrail tracing so you can see exactly what happened at each step. Makes debugging a lot less painful.  https://github.com/crewAIInc/crewAI/releases/tag/1.14.0

